Posts.Content: Jul 8, 2018 08:43PM Jewel259 wrote: Right On Sister! Gaining knowledge is smart and it is also a sign of stability. Knowledge is taking control of your journey and an excellent coping skill. However, we all need counseling with a cancer diagnosis and this forum provides that to a degree. I too am waiting for my oncotype dx score with a high K1-67. Turns out they didn’t do it. Meeting with the medical oncologist in two days. God Bless every woman on this site and a great big thank you for all recommendations.
